.TH XARGS(1),User Commands,XARGS(1)

.SH NAME
xargs - build and execute command lines from standard input

.SH SYNOPSIS
xargs [-n maxargs] [command [arg ...]]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The xargs utility reads whitespace-delimited tokens from standard input and executes the given command with those tokens appended as arguments. If no command is given, echo is used.

xargs runs the command repeatedly until all tokens from stdin have been consumed.

The total argument buffer is limited to 192 bytes. If this limit is reached mid-token-list, the command is flushed and restarted with the base command arguments.

.SH OPTIONS
-n maxargs: Run the command after at most maxargs tokens have been read from stdin, even if more tokens remain.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The xargs utility exits 0 on success, and >0 if an error occurs.

.SH EXAMPLES
Run echo with all tokens from stdin:

$ echo "one two three" | xargs echo

Delete a list of files:

$ cat filelist.txt | xargs rm

Process two files at a time:

$ cat filelist.txt | xargs -n 2 process
